runtime: fix segfault due to missing argv on musl-linux c-archive

Upstream: Go PR #69325 <https://github.com/golang/go/pull/69325>
          (Gerrit CL for Go issue #13492); not yet merged upstream.
Context:  nchat issue #204 <https://github.com/d99kris/nchat/issues/204>,
          see doc/MUSLGO.md.

Rebased onto go1.26.3 (the Go shipped by alpine:3.24, used by
Dockerfile.alpine). Apply with: patch -p1 -d "$GOROOT" < this-file

Local deviations from the upstream PR (both required on go >= 1.26):
1. getGodebugEarly() now returns (string, bool) and strips the
   "GODEBUG=" prefix; the musl branch is adapted accordingly.
2. getGodebugEarly() is called before mallocinit() in schedinit(), so
   the upstream musl branch (which allocates via append/make in
   readNullTerminatedStringsFromFile) crashes in mallocgc. The early
   lookup is replaced by getGodebugEarlyFromProc(), which reads
   /proc/self/environ into a static buffer and returns a no-copy
   string. goargs()/goenvs() run after mallocinit() and keep the
   upstream approach.

Runtime requirement: /proc must be mounted (values are read from
/proc/self/cmdline and /proc/self/environ on musl).

